{
  "doc_id": "14636",
  "text": "Multiple sensory systems as well as abiotic and biotic inputs are used in regulating expression from group I hrp regulons. Among these sensory systems are Lon, GacA, HrpXY, rsmA/B, HrpRS, HrpV, HrpG and quorum-sensing components [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Here, we study the HrpRS, HrpV and HrpG components of Ps DC3000 and report: direct evidence for a single mixed composition functional hexameric HrpRS complex; that HrpR and HrpS each contact σ",
